Taco bang-bang time üî´, comparing two Logan taquerias to see what‚Äôs up. Restaurant Traspasada versus Carniceria Guanajuato. Two taquerias enter the cage, one taq leaves.

The best of the bunch was the Traspasada carne asada taco, more tender & quite a bit better than Guanajuato‚Äôs. The Guanajuato lomo taco was tasty though. Al pastor is pretty subjective in terms of if you‚Äôre feeling the spicing of that specific marinade or not.

Traspasada wins this taco battle by a wide margin. Just learned Traspasada/Las Asadas/ and La Pasadita are owned by members of the same family. That‚Äôs why they all make salsa negra. Blew my mind, some Morpheus red pill news.
